1
00:00:00,083 --> 00:00:03,625
Less than a week later, the interrogator came back to me

2
00:00:03,875 --> 00:00:08,458
He asked, What’s new? Do you need anything?

3
00:00:08,750 --> 00:00:13,833
I said, Nothing new, but I want to see my father, just once

4
00:00:14,708 --> 00:00:18,083
He said, You’ll see him today

5
00:00:18,416 --> 00:00:20,666
So I went to see my father, and through the door

6
00:00:21,041 --> 00:00:23,083
I spoke to him and asked how he was

7
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:26,791
I reassured him that I was fine

8
00:00:27,041 --> 00:00:30,708
And lifted his spirits a bit so he wouldn’t worry too much about me

9
00:00:30,875 --> 00:00:32,750
Then I returned to my cell after five minutes

10
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:41,125
About a week later

11
00:00:42,291 --> 00:00:44,708
It seemed to me that a senior ISIS official came to the prison

12
00:00:44,916 --> 00:00:48,750
Because they started cleaning and tidying the facilities

13
00:00:49,208 --> 00:00:50,791
The official made a tour around us

14
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:53,250
Asking, What’s your name? What’s your case?

15
00:00:54,250 --> 00:00:56,375
He asked me, Do you need anything?

16
00:00:57,333 --> 00:01:00,166
I explained my situation and asked about my fate

17
00:01:00,375 --> 00:01:02,333
He said, Don’t worry, everything’s fine

18
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:04,500
Then he repeated, Do you want anything else?

19
00:01:04,666 --> 00:01:05,666
I said, I want to see my father

20
00:01:06,583 --> 00:01:08,000
He asked, When was the last time you saw him?

21
00:01:08,208 --> 00:01:10,041
I answered, Once, and for five minutes

22
00:01:10,791 --> 00:01:11,750
He said, Alright

23
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:16,958
Then placed me with my father in the
same group cell, where I found him alone

24
00:01:19,250 --> 00:01:20,583
The official continued his tour

25
00:01:20,750 --> 00:01:22,750
And we could hear the voices of my brother and cousins

26
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:24,458
As he asked them about their needs

27
00:01:25,583 --> 00:01:29,208
When I saw my father, he hugged
me and started crying. He was fasting

28
00:01:30,333 --> 00:01:33,250
It was Thursday, and we broke our fast together

29
00:01:34,666 --> 00:01:36,875
We didn’t sleep all night

30
00:01:37,083 --> 00:01:38,750
Because of our long conversation
and how much we missed each other

31
00:01:39,083 --> 00:01:42,708
We tried to lift our spirits and comfort each other

32
00:01:43,083 --> 00:01:45,208
We talked about the charges brought against us

33
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:47,500
My father’s charge was that he once said

34
00:01:47,750 --> 00:01:50,958
That if a military operation began against ISIS in the area

35
00:01:51,166 --> 00:01:54,166
He would be ready to arm 500 fighters

36
00:01:54,875 --> 00:01:57,416
Which was, of course, a fabricated and false accusation

37
00:01:57,791 --> 00:02:03,250
They demanded he bring 500 rifles

38
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:07,250
My father, in turn, demanded

39
00:02:07,541 --> 00:02:08,916
That they bring witnesses to these accusations

40
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:10,833
They told him, Your witness is here

41
00:02:11,375 --> 00:02:12,916
He said, Bring him, I have no problem

42
00:02:13,291 --> 00:02:14,958
After the interrogation ended

43
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:19,708
One of the prisoners told him the name of the witness

44
00:02:20,041 --> 00:02:22,250
And informed my father about it

45
00:02:22,833 --> 00:02:25,375
My father told his fellow prisoners

46
00:02:25,541 --> 00:02:27,750
About the accusation against him

47
00:02:28,041 --> 00:02:29,541
And that there was a witness

48
00:02:30,333 --> 00:02:32,416
He repeatedly asked for the witness
to be brought, but they never did

49
00:02:32,666 --> 00:02:34,416
When one of my father’s cellmates was released

50
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:35,625
He told the story to the supposed witness

51
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:37,458
Who later came to the prison

52
00:02:37,666 --> 00:02:40,791
And confirmed that he had not witnessed what my father said

53
00:02:41,541 --> 00:02:43,916
That the entire accusation had no basis in truth

54
00:02:44,625 --> 00:02:46,291
But ISIS members expelled him

55
00:02:46,416 --> 00:02:48,166
Telling him that it was none of his concern

56
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:51,875
It became clear that the accusation was fabricated

57
00:02:52,375 --> 00:02:54,083
And my father’s imprisonment was purely arbitrary
